<UserControl xmlns="https://github.com/avaloniaui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
             xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
             xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
             mc:Ignorable="d" d:DesignWidth="800" d:DesignHeight="450"
             x:Class="StellarMVVM_2024.Views.finance_accounts_archive_screen">
	<UserControl.Styles>
		<StyleInclude Source="/Styles/archive info styles/finance_accounts_archive_stylesheet.axaml"/>
	</UserControl.Styles>
	<Panel Background="Pink">
		<StackPanel
			HorizontalAlignment="Center"
			Name="financeAccountsArchiveStackPanel">
			<TextBlock
				Classes="title"
				PointerReleased="returnPrevious">
				finance accounts
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				1. many different types of bank/finance accounts for different purposes
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				2. a common type is a savings account, where you put money into it and it accumulates interest
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				3.savings accounts have a limit of how many times you can withdraw monthly
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				4. a penalty will occur if you withdraw too many times from a savings account
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				5. another common type of account is a checking account
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				6.checking accounts allow you to withdraw money, like for a debit card or ATM
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				7. if you withdraw more money than what's in your account, an overdraft fee will occur (like a penalty)
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				8. there are also accounts specialized for retirement funds, like an IRA
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				9.  savings accounts can be used as investment accounts, though growth can be slow
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				10. accounts can also be joint, meaning multiple people manage it
			</TextBlock>
		</StackPanel>

	</Panel>

</UserControl>
